race.comment: I'M HELRO (7) won two jumpouts and then was heavily bet at Horsham on debut, but faded late after stalking the lead. She's sure to have taken improvement from that and deserves another chance. BUTTERCUP (5) placed at Casterton as a short-priced favourite before the spell and raced wide without cover at Warrnambool first-up. She was well in the market and will be better for that outing. She's capable of using the inside barrier to her advantage and has winning claims. WEMBLEY STADIUM (4) resumes for the Archibald yard and has looked talented at the jumpouts. The well-bred gelding maps for the run of the race, and a bold effort is on the cards. UNDER CONTROL (14) debuts and has been well educated. Won his latest jumpout and on profile she has to be kept very safe.
